1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
2 apple
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 Cucumber
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt
1 Celery
1 Carrot
1 Courgette
1 packet Basic Sponge Mix
1 drizzle olive oil
1 piece egg
½ cup milk

• Preheat oven to 200°C/180°C fan-forced.
• Grease and line an 8-12 hole muffin tray with baking paper.
• Grate courgette and carrot.

• In a large bowl, add basic sponge mix, garlic & herb seasoning, the egg,
milk, Greek-style yoghurt and 2 tbs of olive oil. Mix until just combined.
• Add courgette, carrot and shredded Cheddar cheese, then stir until just
combined.
TIP: Be careful not to overmix the batter!

• Divide batter evenly between muffin tray holes, filling each to the top (you
should get 8-12 muffins).
• Bake until golden brown, 20-25 minutes.
• Set aside to cool slightly in tin.

• Meanwhile, cut apple into wedges. Slice celery and cucumber into sticks.
• Divide hidden veggie savoury muffins and snacks between lunch boxes.
Enjoy!